      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RIPPLES NZ (8) led from one spot wider than this in a resuming win at this circuit and distance two back before chasing a smart mare as runner-up last start. Better off back against the fillies and should be nearing her peak third up. SPARKLING SEA (10) was too good in her resuming win at Wagga, drawing on the back row and racing three wide without cover before scoring easily. Draws out but came from this barrier to win at this circuit and distance twice last campaign and was runner up in a Group 1 the only time she has been beaten here. Can threaten. HAVTIMETODREAM NZ (6) has won her three Brisbane starts since switching from NZ to Chantal Turpin. Tackles some stronger rivals but she has been kept up to the mark with a trial win and is a filly on the up. PERFECTDELIGHT (11) draws much wider than in her resuming win but wasn't far behind SPARKLING SEA when ending the last campaign with a G1 placing at this circuit and distance. CAPTURE OUR HEART NZ (2) is building nicely and draws well.",
